<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880819-0123 </DOCNO><HL> Initial State Jobless Claims Declined in Aug. 6 Week </HL><SO> </SO><CO> LABOR </CO><IN> ECO EMI </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Initial claims for regular state unemployment benefits fell to a seasonally adjusted 311,000 during the week ended Aug. 6 from 331,000 the previous week, the Labor Department said.    The number of persons receiving regular state benefits in the week ended July 30 increased to a seasonally adjusted 2,149,000, or 2.2% of those covered by unemployment insurance, from 2,099,000 in the previous week, when the rate was 2.1%.    Counting all state and federal benefit programs, the number of people receiving unemployment benefits in the week ended July 30 rose to 2,049,700 from a revised 2,030,700 a week earlier. These figures aren't seasonally adjusted. </TEXT></DOC>